&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate brings deep expertise in peptide chemistry, bioorthogonal and click conjugation strategies, and cleavage chemistry development — with a track record of building new chemical methods for complex, multi-component systems. You combine a synthetic chemist&#39;s mechanistic rigor with sensitivity to how chemistry performs inside a demanding multi-cycle assay environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a full-time, exempt, in-person position with work conducted at our Berkeley, CA location.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
